```json
{
  "application": "slurm",
  "details": {
    "job_name": "slepc@3.16.0",
    "account": "use300",
    "partition": "ind-gpu-shared",
    "nodes": 1,
    "tasks_per_node": 1,
    "cpus_per_task": 10,
    "memory": "93G",
    "gpus": 1,
    "time": "00:30:00",
    "output_file": "%x.o%j.%N",
    "system_name": "expanse",
    "spack_version": "0.17.3",
    "spack_instance_name": "gpu",
    "spack_instance_dir": "${HOME}/cm/shared/apps/spack/${SPACK_VERSION}/${SPACK_INSTANCE_NAME}",
    "scheduler_module": "slurm",
    "intel_license_file": "40000@elprado.sdsc.edu:40200@elprado.sdsc.edu",
    "spack_package": "slepc@3.16.0",
    "spack_compiler": "intel@19.1.3.304",
    "spack_variants": "~arpack ~blopex ~cuda ~rocm",
    "spack_dependencies": "^petsc@3.16.1/$(spack find --format '{hash:7}' petsc@3.16.1 % ${SPACK_COMPILER} ~mpi ~complex)",
    "spack_spec": "${SPACK_PACKAGE} % ${SPACK_COMPILER} ${SPACK_VARIANTS} ${SPACK_DEPENDENCIES}"
  }
}
```

The script is running under the **slurm** workload manager. It uses the **spack** package manager to install the **slepc** package with specific compiler, variants, and dependencies. The script also utilizes **intel** compiler and **petsc** as a dependency. The script runs on the **expanse** system and utilizes a **gpu** resource. It uses a **slurm** scheduler module and defines environment variables to ensure proper execution.  The script also uses the **time** command for performance measurement.
